OL,3,CFamilies in fight for law change to
OL,4,Cget essential care for loved ones
OL,6,FShe told UTV she felt the withdrawal
OL,7,Fof the provision was "not fair" and
OL,8,Fshe had talked to others who are in a
OL,9,Fsimilar position and afraid to speak
OL,10,Fout in case they lose further support.
OL,12,FShe said the help of her carer, gave
OL,13,Fher daughter some independence.
OL,15,FShe said a change in the law would
OL,16,Fmake sure it was "legal" for her
OL,17,Fdaughter's carers to carry out the
OL,18,F"right standard of care".
